programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Tent City Jail, Phoenix, Arizona, USA
programme.desc: Old army tents left over from the Korean War house prisoners instead of cells. The Sheriff is a hard man who refuses to spend any more than he has to on his prisoners. Harassment and humiliation is a part of everyday life at Tent City.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Antanimora Prison, Madagascar
programme.desc: Desperate overcrowding, rats, and disease come standard in Antanimora Prison. Surrounded by the capital Antananarivo, it's bursting at the seams. It was originally built for 800 prisoners, but now it contains more than 3,000 prisoners.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: A hairy, aggressive monster is said to haunt northern New Zealand. The Maori named it Moehau, in honor of the highest peak in a nearby mountain range. This half-man, half-gorilla is a true New Zealand legend, just as Bigfoot is for North Americans.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: A monster has terrorized Belize for centuries. It is described as a small man, three-feet tall, with an ugly face, hands without thumbs and inverted feet. According to legend it wears a red hat, dresses in animal skins and carries a menacing machete.

programme.title: Caught on Camera
programme.desc: In one year alone, more than a million crimes were committed on London area roads. Fortunately, CCTV cameras help bring those responsible to justice.

programme.title: Caught on Camera
programme.desc: Host Nick Wallis visits CCTV centers that work to control the rising rise in gun and knife violence in the UK.

programme.title: Climate Challenge: Greenland and Maldives
programme.desc: Travel to Greenland and the Maldives. Greenland is one of the last pristine places on Earth, and the Maldives, a tropical paradise. Although over 10,500 km apart, their futures are intwined. They are positioned in the front-line of the Climate Challenge.

programme.title: Climate Challenge: Uganda and California
programme.desc: California is experiencing horrible droughts. Uganda is falling victim to torrential rain and landslides. Both areas, though completely different, are suffering the same problems. Complete changes in weather patterns due to climate change.

programme.title: Climate Challenge: Costa Rica and Norway
programme.desc: Costa Rica, a spectacular haven of wildlife, rich forestry and natural resources. Northernmost Norway in the arctic where the effects of climate change are felt first. These two contrasting countries are both desperate to survive the Climate challenge.

programme.title: Surviving the Lagoon
programme.desc: In the heart of the a vast ocean, the atolls of the Pacific are like oasis in a sprawling desert. Each one contains a unique and breathtaking environment. Where the reef breaks, the ecosystem of the lagoon flourishes.

programme.title: Swimming with Legends
programme.desc: The largest creatures on Earth live underwater. Their sheer size has always triggered our imagination. In murky waters or inaccessible places, we ignored their true nature and created legends. How can we decipher their underwater secrets?

programme.title: Human Prey: Killers on the Loose
programme.desc: Gary Brown's visit to an African chimp sanctuary becomes a deadly struggle when he and his guide are attacked by the colony's escaped alpha male. Idaho Zoo's 'Feast for the Beast' fundraiser takes a bloody turn when a 600-pound Siberian tiger breaks free.

programme.title: Human Prey: Killers of the Savannah
programme.desc: Focused on helping a pregnant, wounded lioness, an unarmed South African conservationist unwittingly ends up face-to-face with one of the pride's aggressive, young males. During his Zambezi River adventure, a pilot is attacked by a hungry hyena.

programme.title: Human Prey: Killer Bears
programme.desc: While hiking through Montana's Glacier National Park, Johan and Jenna Otter are attacked by a raging grizzly intent on protecting her cubs. In a remote British Columbia nature park, Patti and Kelly McConnell are mauled by a hungry 400-pound black bear.

programme.title: Aerial Odyssey: Germany From Above
programme.desc: This spectacular film takes the viewer on a journey of a special kind - discovering Germany from a birds-eye-view, showcasing impressive and enchanting images of a beautiful land. See Germany as you have never seen it before.

programme.title: Ellis Island: History
programme.desc: About 12 million emigrants landed on Ellis Island; First outpost of the American federal immigration station in the New York Bay, the ultimate gateway to the United States of America. However, when they first arrive, their fates do not belong to them.

programme.title: A Ripple of Hope
programme.desc: In the wake of the assassination of Martin Luther King, Robert F. Kennedy made a speech: a moving, off the cuff plea for peace and reconciliation. Risking his own life and defying city officials, Kennedy helped Indianapolis avert certain violence.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: San Pedro Prison, La Paz, Bolivia
programme.desc: Imagine a prison so fierce that guards stay outside for fear of their lives. Inside, the prisoners are in control: murderers, violent offenders, drug bosses. The inmates rule and anarchy prevails. Only the strongest survive this lawless place.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Dallas County Jail, Dallas. Texas, USA
programme.desc: The Dallas County Jail in Texas - a supersized facility with beds for 7,100 inmates. The biggest threat in the prison? Turf wars. With the surplus of inmates, there is less space to divide up between them, leading to relentless gang warfare.

programme.title: Good Time Max
programme.desc: Suspenseful, twisty and starring award-winning James Franco (127 Hours). Meet brothers Adam and Max. Leading a successful medical career, Adam prescribes drugs, while hedonistic Max, deals drugs.

programme.title: Cruel Intentions
programme.desc: Two vicious step-siblings of an elite Manhattan prep school make a wager: to deflower the new headmaster's daughter before the start of term. Starring: Sarah Michelle Gellar, Ryan Phillippe, Reese Witherspoon.

programme.title: Fulfillment
programme.desc: When a couple wants a baby but the husband cannot produce one, he calls his brother, hoping he will oblige and his wife will agree.

programme.title: The Flight Before Christmas
programme.desc: Starring Mayim Bialik and Ryan McPartlin. Two strangers offer to share the last remaining room at a bed-and-breakfast when a snowstorm strands their flight in Montana on Christmas Eve.

programme.title: Saints And Soldiers 3
programme.desc: Four American soldiers and one Brit fighting in Europe during World War II struggle to return to Allied territory after being separated from U.S. forces during the historic Malmedy Massacre.

programme.title: A Gift Wrapped Christmas
programme.desc: Starring Meredith Hagner, Travis Milne, and Beverley Mitchell. Personal shopper Gwen's new client is a workaholic single father. When Gwen meets his 7-year-old son, she makes their lacking father-son relationship her Christmas mission.

programme.title: Windstorm
programme.desc: Rebel teen Mika encounters a beautiful, wild stallion named Windstorm at her grandmother's riding school and learns she can communicate with horses.

programme.title: Girl Most Likely
programme.desc: A failed New York playwright awkwardly navigates the transition from Next Big Thing to Last Year's News. Starring: Kristen Wiig, Annette Bening, Matt Dillon, Natasha Lyonne.

programme.title: Christmas in Wonderland
programme.desc: Starring Matthew Knight and Chris Kattan. Three children and their father move from California to Canada. When they go shopping at the mall, they find counterfeit cash, inadvertently help catch crooks, and make a discovery about Santa.

programme.title: Paper Heart
programme.desc: Charlyne Yi embarks on a quest across America to make a documentary about the one subject she doesn't fully understand: love.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Crawling Eye
programme.desc: Things start to look eerily familiar to scientists Crevett and Brooks when mountain climbers begin losing their heads in the Trollenberg Mountains.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Slime People
programme.desc: The crew puts Commando Cody on trial for crimes against reality after watching the sixth episode of Radar Men while slime monsters invade Los Angeles in The Slime People.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Moon Zero Two
programme.desc: Moon Zero Two: The crew stages their own moon landing pageant as they watch the film about an astronaut hired to capture an asteroid made of sapphires.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Untamed Youth
programme.desc: Joel invents a pipe with a smoke detector and a sprinkler system built in for the invention exchange. The guys watch a 1950s teen flick about youths sentenced to manual labor at a cotton farm.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Black Scorpion
programme.desc: Giant scorpions rise out of a volcano and attack Mexico in The Black Scorpion.

programme.desc: There have been many, many Plan 9s all throughout history, some of them more successful than others, all of them terrestrial - it took a man with the vision of Ed Wood to show us the very real horrors of a Plan 9 from Outer Space!

programme.desc: In Machu Pichu, Oggy is appointed to watch over the temple offerings. The cockroaches team up with a crazy conquistador who helps them to get rid of Oggy and steal the offerings. He gets the temple's golden statue in exchange….

programme.desc: It’s the school robot competition and Lola and her friends relentlessly work on their creation. / Lola, who wishes to do some work experience, offers Virginia’s dad, a loyal customer of the twins’ restaurant, to deliver his sushis to his house.

programme.title: Lola & Virginia: On the Sidelines / I Survived 100 Days in San Lorenzo
programme.desc: Lola is captain of the school basketball team. And for the first time in 47 years, the team is in the final! / When Virginia has been in San Lorenzo for 100 days, she gives Lola and her friends a book written by her.

programme.title: Lola & Virginia: Good Morning, San Lorenzo / Love Soap
programme.desc: Lola is the radio host at San Lorenzo college and very popular with the students. Virginia does not view Lola’s success in a favorable light ... / Virginia is having ‘tea’ with her friends from her former school, the highly-prestigious Columbus College.

programme.title: Lola & Virginia: Frog Party / Tyranosaurus Virginia
programme.desc: During a biology lesson, Virginia goes into raptures over a beautiful frog: She wants it for her next fancy dress party. / The twins Agi and Yukio are going to be on a popular science programme on TV. Virginia is green with envy ...

programme.title: Lola & Virginia: Carnival / Frozen Heart
programme.desc: It’s coming up to carnival and all the schools in the city are going to take part in the parade, each one with its float. / A brand new ice-cream parlour has just opened in San Lorenzo, with a special corner for lovers, the ‘Love Seat’.

programme.title: Lola & Virginia: The Olympic Torch / Teacher's Pet
programme.desc: It’s coming up to the city’s School Olympics and the organising committee has decided that the torch-bearer should be a female athlete from San Lorenzo. / Just before she has to hand it in, Lola’s brothers mess up her school assignment ...

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Oggy the Lord of Lightning
programme.desc: Oggy's Viking village implores Thor, the God of Lightning, to protect them from monsters. Thor is super powerful and gets rid of them easily, but Oggy realizes that Thor is scared of cockroaches. Thor lends Oggy his hammer….

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Oggy and the Short-Sighted Cyclops
programme.desc: While seeking his way home, Oggyseus disturbs Poseidon who is having a nap. He wakes up in a fury and triggers off a storm. Oggy's ship ends up on the Cyclops Island, and the crew is in a terrible state... Will Oggyseus and his friends manage to escape?

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Super Temor
programme.desc: The cockroaches are driving Oggy crazy. He goes to a witch-doctor, a curse specialist, who bestows him with a genie called "Super Temor". This creature deals with the cockroaches in a flash, but lingers on with Oggy, behaving in an over-zealous way.

programme.title: Supa Strikas: The End Of Dreams
programme.desc: Big Bo helps local prison inmates by training their soccer team. But Knuckles, a nasty convict, looks just like the great goalkeeper and switches places with Big Bo! How will he escape in time for Supa Strikas’ epic game against the mighty FC Colossus?

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Big Bo Lockdown
programme.desc: Pressure is on as Supa Strikas arrive in Spain to play Barka FC and star striker, Riano. But Shakes gets some training from Riano’s old Coach, Golare, which turns out to be less than helpful!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Instinct Extinct
programme.desc: Supa Strikas face Twisting Tiger’s old team, FC Nakama, but Nakama boss Ura Giri releases a DVD of all Tiger’s secret moves to punish him for leaving the team. Now the famous midfielder needs to find new moves ... and fast!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Between Friends
programme.desc: Supa Strikas travel to Mexico to confront the biggest goalkeeper in the Super League. Shakes uncovers De Los Santos’ past, and makes an amazing discovery in the big man’s hometown: mysterious Aztec ruins ... and the origins of the game itself!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Blasts From The Past
Supa Strikas: Compound Compromised
programme.desc: On a trip to Rio to play Brazilian masters-of-flair, Club Palmentieri, Supa Strikas are demolished in a “friendly” beach game. The only person who can help them is a legend of the game ... who has been missing for thirty years!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: The Lost Star

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Buzzing Around
programme.desc: Marina is in her castle. Everything is calm and luxurious until an annoying fly spoils the atmosphere. Sharko has a hard time helping Marina get rid of it. That's when Zig and Bernie show up, disguised as exterminators….

programme.title: Zig & Sharko
programme.desc: Sharko and Marina are watching a vampire movie, which spooks them. Zig and Bernie decide to use vampire tactics to terrify Sharko and kidnap the mermaid. But it's not easy playing Dracula….

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: King of the Animal World
programme.desc: Giant lizards show up on the beach to protect Zig from any harm. For them the hyena is at the top of the food chain and deserves some respect! Zig is delighted but his bodyguards have other plans….

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: The Toothpaste
programme.desc: When Sharko's asleep, Zig slips a stinky cheese into his mouth. Marina, repulsed by his breath, takes off fast. Just as Zig is about to pounce on her, Sharko takes toothpaste out of his pocket! Problem solved.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: The Curse
programme.desc: A mummy tries - unsuccessfully - to sell charms and knick-knacks on the beach. When the mummy sees Zig (in dreadful shape), it thinks it has found the perfect pigeon, and fobs off a 'magical' talisman ….

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Rolling, Action!
programme.desc: To trap Marina, Bernie organizes a movie shoot where Zig and the mermaid play their real life roles for the camera. Sharko is furious: he isn't selected for the cast! But Bernie is going to take his director's job too seriously.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: The Fall
programme.desc: Zig uses a human-cannonball stunt starring Marina as the ball, aiming to fire her into his cargo-plane. But Sharko is watching over her. The canon explodes and shoots all three of them into space. A long fall back to Earth ensues, full of surprises.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Some killers are so troubled that their actions are almost impossible to comprehend. Welcome to the shadow land of the insane and psychopathic as we enter the haunting world of the disturbed.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Love and desire are powerful currents that surge through human affairs. When they run off course, the results can be deadly.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: These deadly women were consumed by obsessions that overtook their minds and their lives. These women all had a fatal fixation.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Revenge is one of the oldest motives for murder, but these cases are much more than an “eye for an eye.”.

programme.title: Deadly Women: A Daughter's Revenge
programme.desc: Every day, teenage girls are being scolded by their parents, only to respond with tears and slammed bedroom doors. Some daughters won’t take "no" for an answer, and these girls become deadly.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: A lovely lady with an innocent smile, kind eyes, a charming personality? No one would suspect a woman like that would murder. These women don’t look or behave like killers.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: The heaviest judgments of convicted killers are reserved for those who committed premeditated murder. These women plot and plan. They know the consequences of their actions, but still they go forward to kill.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Under His Control
programme.desc: These are love stories with bleak, bloody endings. Blinded by desire, obsessed and malleable, some women fall into lethal relationships with dangerous, controlling men.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Secrets and Lies
programme.desc: Behind their friendly smiles, deadly women hide histories of bloodshed and murder.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Love Gone Wrong
programme.desc: Love can be beautiful, love can be blind and love can be deadly. Desire and jealousy are powerful forces driving women to dark and horrifying places in their minds.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Married to Murder
programme.desc: To the outside world, their marriages seemed happy. But behind closed doors, there was no domestic bliss. These women wanted out, but getting a divorce wasn’t their preferred option.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Teen Killers
programme.desc: They were too young to drink or vote but they were not too young to commit the most brutal of crimes. Some were driven by pure curiosity: how would it feel to take a life?

programme.title: Deadly Women: Love to Death
programme.desc: Love and money are a beautiful marriage, for the lucky ones they create a life of happiness and ease. Unless the love is of money, the bride is a killer, and the groom their victim.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Kill Their Own
programme.desc: A mother's most basic instinct is to protect her children, to put their needs above her own desire for money, freedom and men. But these deadly women break that sacred bond when they turn against that natural instinct and kill their own offspring.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: In some cases, the transformation from everyday woman to brutal killer is activated by a man. A boyfriend or husband can become the focus of a deadly obsession.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Psychopathic killers lurk in society, mostly acting alone. Sometimes fate brings them into contact with another person who shares their cold power to kill.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: We want to believe that all women would give their lives to protect their children. But there are horrifying cases when a mother will turn against her natural instinct and kill her own flesh and blood.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: The mind of a female killer is shaped by a complex cocktail of influences. Do people become that way, driven by horrendous events in their lives? Or are some killers born bad?

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Blood ties are strong ties, sometimes strong enough to pull a person into a murderous conspiracy. When a family member wields his or her power, the result can be death.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: The path towards revenge can sometimes lead to murder. It can be quick, fiery and violent. It can also be a dish served cold, the product of a calm, calculated plot.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: While their sisters chose a life of sensible, suburban motherhood, these deadly women chose a life of crime. They lived with the thrills, the danger and the deadly consequences of being outlaws.

programme.title: Deadly Women

programme.title: The FBI Files: Melissa Brannen: Missing
programme.desc: In 1989, residents of a close-knit apartment community in Virginia gathered for a holiday celebration. For Tammy Brannen and five-year-old daughter Melissa, Christmas was always a special time. Then, without warning, the little girl was gone.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The Unabomber
programme.desc: For nearly two decades a mathematical genius with delusions of single-handedly destroying industrial society, planted or mailed powerful bombs to unsuspecting innocent victims.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The Murdering Cowboy
programme.desc: The sun set on the Wild West long ago, but some people refused to notice. Claude Dallas was one of them. A wily trapper, Dallas typified the rugged individualism that forged this country. He went too far when he killed two game wardens in 1981.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The World Trade Center Bombing
programme.desc: Terrorist bombings are what happen in other countries. Not here in the United States. And yet, in 1993, it happened in New York City.

programme.title: The FBI Files: John Gotti: Convicted
programme.desc: John Gotti was ambitious, powerful and ruthless. He ruled with flash and conspicuous style, playing celebrity with the media and cat and mouse with the FBI. They called John Gotti the Teflon Don. Serious charges just wouldn't stick.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The True Story of Mississippi Burning
programme.desc: Philadelphia, Mississippi, 1964. A sleepy southern town steeped in tradition finds itself targeted for invasion.

programme.title: The FBI Files: A Model Killer
programme.desc: It's a model's job to rivet the public's attention. But in 1984, some aspiring models began attracting publicity in a terrible new way.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Hired Gun
programme.desc: When three people were found murdered in their home, it appeared like a burglary gone awry. But a crime this horrific deserved a closer look.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Cat and Mouse
programme.desc: He was a predator, abducting girls and young women from their own front yards in broad daylight. He was a sadist: phoning one victim's family, taunting them, boosting then dashing their hope, and he wouldn't stop until we stopped him.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Cracking The Cartel
programme.desc: A mother and child are kidnapped, a bystander is murdered. Violence such as this shattered a quiet Texas neighborhood and exposed a drug cartel that flourished where it was least expected.

programme.title: The FBI Files: A Stranger in Town
programme.desc: She appeared on the highway in the spring, a young woman, her life cut short, her past and her identity a mystery. Only by finding out who she was could we ever hope to find her killer.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Hunter's Game
programme.desc: In the 1970's and 80s, people went to Alaska looking for a fresh start, to reinvent themselves, or to disappear for a while. Some of those disappearances weren't by choice.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Dixie Mafia
programme.desc: On Mississippi's Gulf Coast, a Judge and his politician wife are murdered in their home. The killer left few clues. It looked like a professional hit, and the investigation led nowhere. But the FBI refused to give up.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Shattered Shield
programme.desc: In a city awash in narcotics the drug lords have all the power even over the police. Corruption in New Orleans grew like cancer, eating away at public safety and threatening to destroy the city. Crooked cops break the laws they were sworn to uphold.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Blood Brothers
programme.desc: When the small community of Noel, Missouri discovered their bank was robbed, they're shocked. When the bank president turned up missing, they're outraged. And when clues began to surface the facts were more terrible than anyone could have guessed.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Crime Spree
programme.desc: They swept through six states like a plague, thrill killers acting without rhyme or reason. They targeted adults and young girls, kidnapping, and murdering. And in their rampage, they left plenty of clues, but moving targets are the hardest to hit.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Family Secrets
programme.desc: A woman and her infant son vanish. The husband is frantic. The clues are scarce, but hopes linger, even as the hours and days tick by without a word. Was she on the run, or the victim of foul play?

programme.title: The FBI Files: Master Plan
programme.desc: Willow Springs, Illinois, seemed like any other quiet Midwestern community. But it was really one of the most corrupt places in the nation. This tiny village, nestled just outside of Chicago, was in the hip pocket of organized crime.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Firefight
programme.desc: In Miami, a gang of robbers targeted banks and armored cars. They carried assault weapons and weren't afraid to use them. They struck during the day, and sometimes twice a day. For awhile, they seemed unstoppable.

programme.title: One California Day
programme.desc: Follow the lives of eight California surfers in One California Day. Produced by Build Worldwide, and Co-Directed by Mark Jeremias (maker of Drive) and Jason Baffa (maker of Singlefin Yellow).

programme.title: Children of the Wind
programme.desc: Children of the Wind tells the story of the Bonaire windsurfers, a group of native Caribbean kids, who under the mentorship of Elvis Martinus, founder of the Bonaire Aquaspeed windsurfing club, overcame insuperable odds.

programme.title: Chapters
programme.desc: Chapters is a collection of stories told by a world class group of surfers. The cast of eight was selected to balance and bridge the gap between loggers and high performance longboarders.

programme.title: Castles In the Sky
programme.desc: It begins with a dream. A vision seeded in your mind. But the next step is the one that counts. The first step. Onto the plane. Into the sky. From that moment on, the journey takes on a life of its own.

programme.title: Alternative Surf Craft
programme.desc: Alternative Surf Craft profiles the surfers on the edge of the sport. These surfers carve their own path riding unique and alternative surf craft.

programme.title: Absolute Mexico
programme.desc: Absolute Mexico The Directors Cut - includes bonus footage not included in the original release. See insane tube rides; interviews with top pro-surfers and gorgeous footage of one of the biggest days ever filmed at Puerto Escondido.

programme.title: Absolute Chile
programme.desc: In this follow-up to Absolute Mexico, director Joshua Pomer explores the northern coast of Chile. There we find an all-star crew heading south for some big wave tow surfing.

programme.title: 1000 Waves to Surfing Glory
programme.desc: 1000 Waves to Surfing Glory is presented in a dream like structure with no distracting titles letting the visual imagery speak freely to your surfing soul and wanderlust.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Back Behind Bars

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: All in the Family

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Mother Courage
programme.desc: Dog knows that crime and drugs not only damage victims but also harm the families of the perpetrators, especially the kids. And both of the fugitives he's chasing today have left shattered families and struggling women in their wake.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Bounty Boot Camp
programme.desc: Jim is a bondsman and longtime friend of Dog. Jim's son has just started in the family business. Today, Jim has asked Dog to track down a potentially dangerous fugitive, and take his son along for some training with the best in the world.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Friends and Neighbors
programme.desc: Dog and his posse head to Colorado for a special mission, to catch Marco, an alleged drug dealer. It's been ten months since Marco went on the lam, and his bondsman stands to lose his family business if Marco is not caught.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Set-Up
programme.desc: The trail is hot and the stakes is high for Dog and the posse. The "Big Fish" in this case is Marco, an alleged drug dealer with a big bond. But a major key to catching him is Elizabeth, who is also a fugitive from the law.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Searchers
programme.desc: Dog is still on the search for the elusive fugitive, Marco. Dog has been tracking him across Colorado, from Grand Junction to Denver, and now a hot tip that a long time associate of his is hiding in Pueblo sends the team racing south.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Buddha's Delight

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Three's Company
programme.desc: This fugitive is hard to pin down in Honolulu's downtown district, moving from hostel to hotel to apartment high-rise. But as the hunt evolves, Dog discovers that this alleged burglar isn't the only family member wanted by the law.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Strip Search
programme.desc: When a stripper goes on the lam, Dog has to bring her in. It's a tough job but somebody has to do it. Thankfully for the team, Lady Luck is presiding over the posse tonight.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Secret Places
programme.desc: When Leland learns that one of his clients with a reputation for stealing has lost her co-signer and could be ready to run, Dog and the crew hop a plane to the Big Island.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Wrong Turn

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Midnight Run
programme.desc: This fugitive has a bad reputation and a knack for running from the law. The pursuit has Dog and team traveling through an urban dystopia of suspicion, false leads and mistrust.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Call Waiting

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Kid Stuff

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Easy Does It

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Ghost Rider

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Back in the Hood

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Bait and Switch
